# UI Dockerfile build context is the *repository root* (the workspace
# lockfile lives there and the SDK build needs offchain/), so a true
# Docker-honored ignore would live at the repo root. This file is kept
# alongside the UI so contributors editing the UI image find it easily;
# the canonical exclude list applies to both Dockerfiles via the root
# .dockerignore Docker actually reads.
#
# Keep this in sync with backend/.dockerignore — same exclusions, same
# constraints (don't exclude artifacts/, that breaks bake).

node_modules
dist
.env
.env.*
.git
.github
*.log
test
docs
papers
crypto/ref/target

# UI-specific bulk: Playwright outputs, vite caches.
ui/playwright-report
ui/test-results
ui/.vite
